{"captured_at": "2026-07-17T13:31:05.714302Z", "created_at": "Sat May 16 12:41:09 +0000 2020", "created_at_iso": "2020-05-16T12:41:09Z", "created_at_ts": 1589632869, "display_name": "Fred Fleitz", "handle": "fredfleitz", "id": "1261637813788971008", "language": "en", "media_json": "[]", "metrics_json": "{\"retweet_count\": 975, \"reply_count\": 344, \"like_count\": 1953, \"quote_count\": 145, \"bookmark_count\": 0, \"view_count\": null}", "source_endpoint": "SyndicationProfile", "tags_json": "[]", "text": "1. My new @foxnews op-ed. Major points: despite false claims by former Obama officials, unmasking names of US citizens from intel reports is NOT routine. Sen. Chris Dodd said in 2005 that unmasking requests were “rarely requested” and made “infrequently”   https://t.co/Zg0xydX1Yk", "tweet_type": "tweet", "urls_json": "[{\"url\": \"https://t.co/Zg0xydX1Yk\", \"expanded_url\": \"https://fxn.ws/2AyRNPo\", \"display_url\": \"fxn.ws/2AyRNPo\"}]", "username": "FredFleitz"}
{"captured_at": "2026-07-17T13:31:05.714302Z", "created_at": "Sat May 16 12:43:17 +0000 2020", "created_at_iso": "2020-05-16T12:43:17Z", "created_at_ts": 1589632997, "display_name": "Fred Fleitz", "handle": "fredfleitz", "id": "1261638351217733635", "language": "en", "media_json": "[]", "metrics_json": "{\"retweet_count\": 132, \"reply_count\": 16, \"like_count\": 421, \"quote_count\": 8, \"bookmark_count\": 0, \"view_count\": null}", "source_endpoint": "SyndicationProfile", "tags_json": "[]", "text": "2. The @nytimes said the same thing about unmaskings in a 2005 article: \"Access to the names may be authorized by the N.S.A. only in response to special requests, and these are not common, particularly from policy makers.”", "tweet_type": "reply", "urls_json": "[]", "username": "FredFleitz"}
{"captured_at": "2026-07-17T13:31:05.714302Z", "created_at": "Sat May 16 12:49:56 +0000 2020", "created_at_iso": "2020-05-16T12:49:56Z", "created_at_ts": 1589633396, "display_name": "Fred Fleitz", "handle": "fredfleitz", "id": "1261640023885205507", "language": "en", "media_json": "[]", "metrics_json": "{\"retweet_count\": 157, \"reply_count\": 10, \"like_count\": 435, \"quote_count\": 3, \"bookmark_count\": 0, \"view_count\": null}", "source_endpoint": "SyndicationProfile", "tags_json": "[]", "text": "3. These 2005 statements were made during @AmbJohnBolton's Senate hearing on his nomination to be UN ambassador. Dems falsely argued at the time that Bolton's request of only 10 unmaskings in 4 years was a gross abuse of intelligence for political purposes.", "tweet_type": "reply", "urls_json": "[]", "username": "FredFleitz"}
{"captured_at": "2026-07-17T13:31:05.714302Z", "created_at": "Sat May 16 12:58:37 +0000 2020", "created_at_iso": "2020-05-16T12:58:37Z", "created_at_ts": 1589633917, "display_name": "Fred Fleitz", "handle": "fredfleitz", "id": "1261642210312937472", "language": "en", "media_json": "[]", "metrics_json": "{\"retweet_count\": 283, \"reply_count\": 17, \"like_count\": 633, \"quote_count\": 14, \"bookmark_count\": 0, \"view_count\": null}", "source_endpoint": "SyndicationProfile", "tags_json": "[]", "text": "4. So then-Senators @JoeBiden and Chris Dodd attacked Bolton for just 10 unmasking requests. But Obama's UN Amb Samatha Power made 260 such requests in 2016, including 7 for @GenFlynn's name between 11/8/16 &amp; 1/12/17.  Yet Dems and the media claim \"nothing to see here.\"", "tweet_type": "reply", "urls_json": "[]", "username": "FredFleitz"}
{"captured_at": "2026-07-17T13:31:05.714302Z", "created_at": "Sat May 16 13:03:14 +0000 2020", "created_at_iso": "2020-05-16T13:03:14Z", "created_at_ts": 1589634194, "display_name": "Fred Fleitz", "handle": "fredfleitz", "id": "1261643373028487169", "language": "en", "media_json": "[]", "metrics_json": "{\"retweet_count\": 128, \"reply_count\": 12, \"like_count\": 397, \"quote_count\": 5, \"bookmark_count\": 0, \"view_count\": null}", "source_endpoint": "SyndicationProfile", "tags_json": "[]", "text": "5. I know how rare unmasking requests were from my work with the CIA. NSA tightened the rules on unmasking after the 2005 Bolton confirmation hearing.  However, the Obama administration weakened them to allow more government employees access to this information.", "tweet_type": "reply", "urls_json": "[]", "username": "FredFleitz"}
{"captured_at": "2026-07-17T13:31:05.714302Z", "created_at": "Sat May 16 13:10:48 +0000 2020", "created_at_iso": "2020-05-16T13:10:48Z", "created_at_ts": 1589634648, "display_name": "Fred Fleitz", "handle": "fredfleitz", "id": "1261645274704986112", "language": "en", "media_json": "[]", "metrics_json": "{\"retweet_count\": 177, \"reply_count\": 18, \"like_count\": 464, \"quote_count\": 9, \"bookmark_count\": 0, \"view_count\": null}", "source_endpoint": "SyndicationProfile", "tags_json": "[]", "text": "8. It is imperative to uncover the extent of the Obama admin's abuse of U.S. intel for political purposes. This must include a full list of every American unmasked from intelligence reports – Trump aides, members of Congress, &amp; ordinary Americans – and who made these requests.", "tweet_type": "reply", "urls_json": "[]", "username": "FredFleitz"}
{"captured_at": "2026-07-17T13:31:05.714302Z", "created_at": "Sat May 16 13:13:53 +0000 2020", "created_at_iso": "2020-05-16T13:13:53Z", "created_at_ts": 1589634833, "display_name": "Fred Fleitz", "handle": "fredfleitz", "id": "1261646052769267712", "language": "en", "media_json": "[]", "metrics_json": "{\"retweet_count\": 141, \"reply_count\": 24, \"like_count\": 472, \"quote_count\": 5, \"bookmark_count\": 0, \"view_count\": null}", "source_endpoint": "SyndicationProfile", "tags_json": "[]", "text": "9. We also need to determine how dozens - maybe 100s - of intel officers agreed to process 100s of Obama admin requests to unmask Trump campaign and transition officials.  Such large numbers of requests were obviously ethically dubious.  Why were no IG complaints filed . . .", "tweet_type": "reply", "urls_json": "[]", "username": "FredFleitz"}
